      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Direct Lending Legislative Action</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The series Legislative Action (1.2 linear feet) includes documents concerning three major pieces of legislation concerning Direct Loans during Thomas Wolanin's tenure with Representative William D. Ford's staff. The first is the Higher Education Amendments of 1992 (PL 102-325). This then set the stage for the Direct Loan Authorization, a subseries covering all legislative action after the HEA Amendment, leading up to and then directly following the beginning of the direct loan program under the Revenue Reconciliation Act of 1993 (PL 103-66). Leading up to Fiscal Year 1996, the direct loan program came under a great deal of pressure. The sub-series Fiscal Year 1996 Budget Reconciliation includes documentation of legislative action during that time. Folders are arranged alphabetically by subject.</p>
        </scopecontent>
